Bash(claude-agent haiku-general "Create pediatric chapter skeleton files and update bibliography:

1. Create ch14c-pediatric-severe.tex with this section structure:
   - \\chapter{Pediatric ME/CFS: Severe and Housebound Cases}
   - \\label{ch:pediatric-severe}
   - Sections: Defining Severe Pediatric ME/CFS, Home-Based Care Considerations, Medical Management \(with subsections: Orthostatic Intolerance, Pain Management, Sleep Optimization, Cognitive Support\), Preventing Complications of Prolonged Bedrest, Educational Continuity, Family Support and Caregiver Coordination, Red Flags and Emergency Protocols, Evidence That Severe Pediatric Disease CAN Reverse

2. Create ch14d-pediatric-ambulatory.tex with this section structure:
   - \\chapter{Pediatric ME/CFS: School-Attending and Ambulatory Cases}
   - \\label{ch:pediatric-ambulatory}
   - Sections: The Early Intervention Imperative, Diagnosis and Assessment \(with subsections: Pediatric Diagnostic Criteria Modifications, Distinguishing ME/CFS from Differential Diagnoses\), School Accommodation Framework \(with subsections: IEP vs. 504 Plan Decision Tree, Specific Accommodations by Symptom, Communication Templates\), Pacing for Children and Adolescents \(with subsections: Age-Appropriate Energy Management, Managing the ""Push Through"" Pressure\), Medical Management \(with subsections: Orthostatic Intolerance, Sleep, Cognitive Symptoms\), Activity and Exercise \(with subsections: Critical Warning: GET Contraindicated, Safe Activity Maintenance\), Social Development Considerations, Long-Term Management and Monitoring, Prognosis Communication

3. Update ms.tex to include these chapters after ch14b by adding:
   \\input{contents/part3-treatment/ch14c-pediatric-severe.tex}
   \\input{contents/part3-treatment/ch14d-pediatric-ambulatory.tex}

4. Add these 6 bibliography entries to references.bib:
   - Rowe 2017 Frontiers in Pediatrics primer
   - CDC Pediatric ME/CFS Guidance 2024
   - PMC7551866 \(Severe ME in Children\)
   - PMC5919160 \(Pediatric Chronic Fatigue Syndrome\)
   - PMC11472415 \(Pediatric POTS Management 2024\)
   - PMC9603696 \(Multi-Disciplinary Rehabilitation for Moderate-Severe Pediatric ME/CFS\)

Use placeholder content marked with % TODO comments where clinical content is needed.")
